The outer-level problem can therefore be described as
\begin{equation}
\min_{\hat{y}} \ \beta_C C(x)+\beta_{GME} GME(x)+\beta_\tau \tau'(x)+\beta_E E(x)
\end{equation}
subject to
\begin{equation}
x^k = {\bf pFBA}(k,\hat{y},c) \;\;\; \forall k \in P.
\end{equation}

